    <releaseNotes>
#### Program
When you use Microsoft Visual C++ 2013, you may encounter the following issues:
* Heap corruption occurs because of a synchronization bug in SetLocale, and this triggers an access violation.
* When you install an updated redistributable package, binaries for non-target architectures are removed. For example, after you install an update for an x86-based application, the x64 Visual C++ 2013 runtime libraries are missing. This fix makes sure that both versions of the Visual C++ redistributable are visible when you add or remove programs after installation of the update.

* Supported Operating Systems: Windows 7 SP1, Windows 8, Windows 8.1, Windows Server 2003, Windows Server 2008 R2 SP1, Windows Server 2008 SP2, Windows Server 2012, Windows Server 2012 R2, Windows Vista SP2, Windows XP
* Known issues: http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=323490
* Additional requirements: Windows Update [KB2883200](http://support.microsoft.com/kb/2883200) is required for:
  * Windows 8.1 ([32-bit](http://www.microsoft.com/download/details.aspx?id=40755), [64-bit](http://www.microsoft.com/download/details.aspx?id=40749))
  * Windows Server 2012 R2 ([64-bit](http://www.microsoft.com/download/details.aspx?id=40774))
    </releaseNotes>
